Mass-conservative theory is a fundamental principle used in various fields, including fluid dynamics and control systems. In the context of liquid level control, it focuses on the conservation of mass within a system, ensuring that the amount of liquid in a tank is accurately accounted for and managed over time. The dynamic volume balance for a cylindrical tank is represented by a linear ordinary differential equation involving the variables liquid height ($H
