While the trial-and-error method (Figure 8) improved the response speed compared to ZN tuning, it still carries the risk of instability if not tuned by an expert. The proposed method, however, transitions smoothly to Steady-State Mode once the level reaches the tolerance band (

    ε

). In this mode, the inflow rate is matched to the outflow rate, enforcing mass balance and ensuring negligible steady-state error with minimal oscillation.

To evaluate performance under nonlinear dynamics, the control strategy was applied to a spherical tank. The mathematical model is derived from Eq. (6). Since the liquid level ($H
